original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.

//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] product_reg;

generating terminal state (main module)

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

generating terminal state (main module)

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.

//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,

    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;

        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end

            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.

//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire reset,

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;

        end
    end

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

    reg [63:0] temp;

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.

//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

generating terminal state (main module)

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] A_reg, B_reg;
    reg [63:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [63:0] product;
    reg [31:0] product_low, product_high;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_low, accumulator_high;
    reg [31:0] sum_low, sum_high;
    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg, sum_high_reg;
    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg_reg, sum_high_reg_reg;
    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg_reg_reg, sum_high_reg_reg_reg;
    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg_reg_reg_reg, sum_high_reg_reg_reg_reg;
    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg, sum_high_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg;
    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg, sum_high_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg;
    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg, sum_high_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg;

    reg [31:0] sum_low_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg, sum_high_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg_reg;

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.

//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;

            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,

generating terminal state (main module)

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire reset,

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.

//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator

generating terminal state (main module)
Getting random terminal state.
original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

Ends with endmodule.
Running functionality check.
//Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);
 
    reg [31:0] product;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_reg;
    reg [31:0] accumulator_next;
 
    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (reset) begin
            accumulator_reg <= 0;
        end
        else begin
            accumulator_reg <= accumulator_next;
        end
    end
 
    always @* begin
        product = A * B;
        accumulator_next = accumulator_reg + product;
    end
 
    assign accumulator = {accumulator_reg, product};
 
endmodule

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.

original text:  //Design a Verilog module for a MAC (Multiplier and Accumulator) unit.
//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
//The accumulated result is stored in an output register, accumulator.
//The module should have a control input, clk (clock), to synchronize the operations.
//The module should have a control input, reset (reset), to reset the accumulated result.
module mac_32(
    input wire clk,
    input wire reset,
    input wire [31:0] A,
    input wire [31:0] B,
    output reg [63:0] accumulator
);

//The MAC unit takes two inputs, A and B, and multiplies them.
//The result of the multiplication is accumulated with a third register, C.
